column1: Conduct and report E-stop test issue
column29:
*Issue: REbus voltage not under 30V within 30s after the SDS E-stop is triggered*

I referred to UL 1741, Section 98.1.2. I initially thought it only applied to PVs, but Nirja confirmed that this is the requirement for all DERs including inverters. She added that if the E-stop switch is intended for a rapid safety shutdown, then it needs to meet requirement in section 98.1.2. 

!image-20240828-141545.png|width=1141,height=695,alt="image-20240828-141545.png"!
